<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-59-1248 </DOCNO><TEXT>The procedures outlined in this chapter are similar to those used whenradiographing adults. The examinations of each area are first listedunder the subheading &quot;Standard Views.&quot; Each of the standard views isthen presented with a summary discussion of patient positioning, centeringpoint, orientation of the central ray, and area to be included withinthe limits of collimation. A section entitled &quot;General Considerations&quot;follows for each study, which amplifies specific applications of restraintand patient care. Included in this section of each discussion are &quot;helpfulhints&quot; that ensure an examination of optimum quality.</TEXT></DOC>